This paper discusses the development of behavior control architectures for autonomous agents, specifically for controlling a humanoid soccer robot. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of state-based and behavior-based approaches, which are common in the fields of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of hierarchical structures and multi-action planning, which are relevant to the fields of Machine Learning (cs.MA) and Learning (cs.LG).
